Most Asked Interview Question
=========================================================

Q. Why is Object Slicing dangerous?

Answer:

Object slicing removes the derived portion of an object
when it is copied into a base object by value. As a
result, derived data members are lost and runtime
polymorphism no longer works because the copied object
is now a pure Base object.***************************VVVVVVIMP

